        <p><i style="font-style: normal;">Description:</i> The IP address to bind to. By default, <MadCap:variable name="General.abbrev"></MadCap:variable> listens on every available interface. Note that this is not the address where messages are accepted from.</p>
        <p>If you specify a multicast bind address and use the <b class="Code">udp</b> transport, <MadCap:variable name="General.abbrev"></MadCap:variable> automatically joins the necessary multicast group. TCP does not support multicasting.</p>
